---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Medical Disclaimer – QuitDr"
  description="QuitDr Medical Disclaimer. Important information about the nature and limitations of our telehealth smoking cessation service."
>
  <section class="page-hero" style="padding:3rem 0;">
    <div class="container">
      <h1>Medical Disclaimer</h1>
      <p>Important information about the nature and limitations of this service.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section" style="padding-top:2rem;">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="legal-content">
        <span class="legal-last-updated">Last updated: April 2026</span>

        <!-- Prominent disclaimer box -->
        <div style="background:#FEF2F2; border:2px solid #FECACA; border-radius:var(--radius); padding:1.75rem; margin-bottom:2.5rem;">
          <h3 style="color:#991B1B; font-size:1.05rem; font-weight:700; margin-bottom:.75rem;">&#9888; Important Notice</h3>
          <p style="color:#7F1D1D; font-size:.95rem; line-height:1.75; margin:0;">
            This service provides general medical support for smoking cessation via telehealth. <strong>Treatments and outcomes vary between individuals.</strong> Medications are prescribed only if clinically appropriate. <strong>Please consult a healthcare professional to determine what is right for you.</strong> Results vary between individuals. This is a telehealth service.
          </p>
        </div>

        <h2>1. Nature of the Service</h2>
        <p>QuitDr is a private telehealth service that facilitates consultations between patients and Australian-registered doctors for the purpose of smoking cessation support. It is not a substitute for in-person medical care where in-person assessment is clinically required.</p>

        <h2>2. No Guarantee of Outcomes</h2>
        <p>QuitDr does not guarantee that use of this service will result in quitting smoking or any specific health outcome. Smoking cessation is a complex process influenced by individual factors including nicotine dependence, mental health, social environment, and personal motivation. Structured support through evidence-based care improves success rates, but individual results will vary.</p>
        <p>Approved language in all QuitDr communications reflects this: we describe our service as "designed to support quitting" and "evidence-based care" — not as a cure or guaranteed solution.</p>

        <h2>3. Medical Advice</h2>
        <p>Information provided on the QuitDr website, in program materials, or through the platform is for general informational purposes only. It does not constitute personalised medical advice. Only your treating doctor — in the context of a telehealth consultation — can provide medical advice specific to your circumstances.</p>

        <h2>4. Medications</h2>
        <p>QuitDr does not directly promote prescription-only medicines. Nicotine replacement therapy (NRT) and pharmacotherapy are:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Presented as "available if clinically appropriate"</li>
          <li>Prescribed solely at the discretion of the treating doctor</li>
          <li>Subject to individual clinical assessment</li>
          <li>Dispensed by a licensed Australian pharmacy under TGA-compliant standards</li>
        </ul>
        <p>Not all patients will receive a prescription. The treating doctor determines clinical appropriateness based on your health history, medications, and individual circumstances.</p>

        <h2>5. Emergency Situations</h2>
        <p>QuitDr is <strong>not</strong> an emergency medical service. If you are experiencing a medical emergency, call <strong>000</strong> immediately. Do not use QuitDr to seek help for urgent or life-threatening conditions.</p>

        <h2>6. Regulatory Compliance</h2>
        <p>QuitDr operates in accordance with:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Therapeutic Goods Administration (TGA) guidelines</li>
          <li>AHPRA advertising guidelines for regulated health services</li>
          <li>Australian Consumer Law</li>
          <li>Privacy Act 1988 (Cth)</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>7. AHPRA Advertising Compliance</h2>
        <p>In compliance with AHPRA advertising guidelines for regulated health services, QuitDr:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Does not use testimonials that imply clinical outcomes</li>
          <li>Does not make claims that the service will "cure" smoking addiction</li>
          <li>Does not use language implying guaranteed results (e.g. "100% success", "guaranteed quit")</li>
          <li>Includes required disclaimers in all health-related advertising materials</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>8. Third-Party Services</h2>
        <p>QuitDr is not responsible for the actions, advice, or services of third-party providers including partner pharmacies. Medication dispensed by partner pharmacies is the responsibility of the dispensing pharmacy under applicable Australian pharmacy and medicines regulation.</p>

        <div class="compliance-box" style="margin-top:2.5rem;">
          <span class="icon">&#128274;</span>
          <span>
            <strong>Required Compliance Disclaimer:</strong> This service provides general medical support for smoking cessation via telehealth. Treatments and outcomes vary between individuals. Medications are prescribed only if clinically appropriate. Please consult a healthcare professional to determine what is right for you. Results vary between individuals. This is a telehealth service.
          </span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
